cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and neural models for interpreting noun compounds. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and semantics, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
